bug.short_desc: qx.ui.form.VirtualSelectBox causes application freeze in Chrome

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1378 Screenshots of frozen VirtualSelectBox
In the current version of Chrome (44.0.2403.125 m), the use of VirtualSelectBox will eventually freeze the application.
The behavior can be observed in any dialog containing a VirtualSelectBox. For example, after opening and closing the dropdown list of a VirtualSelectBox a few times, the application will freeze with the VirtualSelectBox expanded (see screen1.png). It is still possible to move the dialog around but the dropdown list will remain hovering where it was without allowing any interaction (see screen2.png). Occasionally, rather that freezing with the dropdown list in-place, the application will freeze with a blank dropdown list in the upper left corner of the browser (see screen3.png).
The issue can be reproduced in the qooxdoo demo browser. Simply open the VirtualSelectBox demo:
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/5.1/demobrowser/#virtual~SelectBox.html
Then go to the playground (important!) and starting clicking on the down arrows of the displayed VirtualSelectBoxes. After clicking a few dozen times, the application will eventually freeze (see screen4.png).
Basically this means that any application using VirtualSelectBox will freeze after a few minutes of use.
Note that we have only reproduced this behavior on Chrome. Interestingly, once the developer console is open, the bug doesn't occur :)
The bug can be reproduced in multiple qooxdoo versions, for example in 3.5, 4.1, and 5.1.

Strange indeed, thanks for the report.
Could you figure out a scenario to more easily reproduce the issue (i.e. less or more specific clicks)? As Chrome 44 is the only browser currently known to cause issues, have you also tried if Chrome Canary (albeit unstable) is affected. Could possibly be a regression in Chrome 44 ...
As with the current version of Chrome this bug doesn't exist any more. So the issue seems to be resolved...
Thanks Stoyan for the follow-up! Resolving this as a regression in Chrome 44.
